Introduction - Welcome to BellaBeat Data Analysis Project

BellaBeat is a high-tech company that manufactures health-focused smart products. Collecting data on activity, sleep, stress, and reproductive health has allowed Bellabeat to empower women with knowledge about their own health and habits. Since it was founded in 2013, Bellabeat has grown rapidly and quickly positioned itself as a tech-driven wellness company for women.

Business Task

Analyse Fitbit data to gain insight on possible growth opportunities for Bellabeat and improve it’s marketing strategy.

Data Source

The data used in this project comes from the Fitbit Fitness Tracker Data on kaggle.https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/arashnic/fitbit This Kaggle data set contains personal fitness tracker from thirty fitbit users. Thirty eligible Fitbit users consented to the submission of personal tracker data, including minute-level output for physical activity, heart rate, and sleep monitoring. It includes information about daily activity, steps, and heart rate that can be used to explore users’ habits.

There is a few things we can learn from this summary:

  1. Having a good flexibility may help reduce stiffness, prevent injuries, and maintain a good range of motion in the joints, therefore the CDC recommends 10 000 Steps each day. Here the average user has 9373 steps each day which is below that mark.

  2. This also shows that the participants average 722.7 minutes in sedentary time which is equivalent to 12 hours. Science shows that higher levels of total sitting time were associated with increased risk in diabetes. Therefore a lot of time is spent on sedentary than recommended. Link here:https://ijbnpa.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12966-020-01044-0

  3. We also see that participants spend about 7hours on average sleeping, which is good per health recommendations.

  4. Average time spent in bed is also 7.6 which is not too high compared to the time spent sleeping. That means users do not spend too much time awake in bed.

  5. Average weight of participants is 139

Visualizing The Data

In this section we are going to visualize data to see trends and relationships between variables to gain more insight.

Relationship Between Active Minutes and Calories Burnt

## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

Based on this figure we see a positive relationship, the more active the participant was the more calories they burned.

Relationship Between Minutes a Sleep and Time in Bed

## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'
## Warning: Removed 971 rows containing non-finite values (stat_smooth).
## Warning: Removed 971 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

Based on this graph we do see a positive relationship the more time spent in bed the more sleeping time the user got.

Relationship Between Total Steps and Calories

## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

Here we see that the more steps done the more calories burned, we can also see from the graph that the highest calories burned are by users who at least do 10000 to 15000 steps a day.

Relationship Between Weight and Calories

There is a positive relationship between the two, the more calories burnt the more weight one loses. Reducing calories is recommended by CDC to reduce weight. Link here: https://www.cdc.gov/healthyweight/calories/index.html

Recommendations For the Bellabeat App

  1. Incorporate a feature that recommends good nutrition with less calories intake.

  2. Encourage users to get 10 000 steps a day, this could be done by means of alert notifications, and by giving users a weekly report of how they have been doing on their physical activities. 10 000 is CDC recommended steps a day.

  3. Encourage more users to engage in vigorous activities by tracking their activity levels and reminding them to do so by means of alert notifications when they do not reach a certain time limit.

  4. There is a lot of time spent on Sedentary time, add a mechanism to notify users to engage in an active activity after a certain time of sedentary minutes have been reached. Also the app could suggest some vigorous activities to users, This could be accomplished by adding some AI features to the app.

  5. Alert users of when they have been in bed for a long time.
